    correct_option_index: 0,
    explanation: "The invalid structure “All pianos are musical instruments; guitars are musical instruments; therefore guitars are pianos” fails because musical instruments acts as an undistributed middle.",
    detailedExplanationBeginner: "Here the middle term “musical instruments” is not distributed. Knowing that guitars belongs to the musical instruments category tells us nothing about whether guitars belongs to the pianos subset; musical instruments almost certainly includes entities outside pianos.",
    detailedExplanationIntermediate: "Form: All pianos are musical instruments (A), Guitars are musical instruments (A), therefore guitars are pianos (A). This is the invalid AAA-2 form. The middle term musical instruments is predicate in both premises and therefore never distributed, violating Rule 2 of the categorical syllogism.",
    detailedExplanationExpert: "AAA-2 is one of the classic invalid categorical forms. The middle term “musical instruments” appears as predicate of two A propositions, never distributed. Venn-diagram analysis shows that the premises pianos ⊆ musical instruments and guitars ⊉ musical instruments do not force guitars into pianos.",
    questionFormat: "standard"
