    detailedExplanationBeginner: "Here the middle term “predators” is not distributed. Knowing that wolves belongs to the predators category tells us nothing about whether wolves belongs to the lions subset; predators almost certainly includes entities outside lions.",
    detailedExplanationIntermediate: "Form: All lions are predators (A), Wolves are predators (A), therefore wolves are lions (A). This is the invalid AAA-2 form. The middle term predators is predicate in both premises and therefore never distributed, violating Rule 2 of the categorical syllogism.",
    detailedExplanationExpert: "AAA-2 is one of the classic invalid categorical forms. The middle term “predators” appears as predicate of two A propositions, never distributed. Venn-diagram analysis shows that the premises lions ⊆ predators and wolves ⊉ predators do not force wolves into lions.",
