    detailedExplanationBeginner: "The undistributed-middle fallacy is subtle here because the premises may be true while the conclusion is false. The logical form fails, regardless of factual truth. particles with positive charge is the middle term and must be distributed at least once for a valid connection, but it is not.",
    detailedExplanationIntermediate: "AAA-2 is always invalid. The middle term particles with positive charge appears in predicate position of an A proposition twice, so it is never distributed. No valid categorical syllogism has two universal-affirmative premises with an undistributed middle.",
    detailedExplanationExpert: "Venn-diagram proof: protons ⊆ particles with positive charge and positrons ⊉ particles with positive charge. The set positrons could be entirely inside particles with positive charge but still not overlap with protons. The conclusion positrons ⊆ protons is not entailed. This violates the dictum de omni et nullo.",
