    detailedExplanationExpert: "The form AAA-3 fails the distribution test: politicians is distributed in the conclusion (A proposition distributes subject) but undistributed in the minor premise (A proposition does not distribute predicate). This is one of the most common illicit-minor mistakes in natural-language reasoning.",
