    detailedExplanationIntermediate: "Formal counterexample: let animals = (1, 2, 3, 4, 5), protected by law = (1, 2, 3, 4) (80% of animals), and birds = 5 (a subset of animals entirely outside protected by law). Then premises are true but “most birds are protected by law” is false.",
