    explanation: "The quantifier “few” expresses a small proportion, but the inference that “few corporations are sustainable” does not follow. The corporations that are not environmentally responsible might still be sustainable, possibly a large number.",
    detailedExplanationBeginner: "From “few A are B” we know |A ∩ B| is small relative to |A|. From “all B are C” we know B ⊆ C. But the A’s outside B may be largely C, making “few A are C” false. The quantifier does not transmit.",
