    detailedExplanationExpert: "The fallacy is a quantifier-scope error with the pseudiquantifier “few.” Even though B ⊆ C, the A’s outside B have an unrestricted relationship with C. The proportion of A that is C depends on the proportion of A outside B that is also C, which is not constrained by the premises.",
